        "checksum": "308e11ad4efc77dbe6462c5fdf19a826492e01e438a0796d40cec30cbade11af_1_1_1_0__1",
        "ggU7cTwtojF_text": "<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:px;\">A Guide To Your SerlinoLab Eye Cream</span>",
        "ggBe0DJx3pQ_text": "<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:px;\">Where to apply it, how much, and why technique matters more than quantity.</span>",
        "gg7pGzZg7y3_text": "<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:px;\">How To Use It</span>",
        "ggt5W7ctjdK_text": "Keep it in the fridge",
        "gg9KjE6e4-X_text": "<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:px;\"><strong>Keep it in the fridge</strong></span>",
        "ggW5doHsOy8_text": "<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">The cold reduces puffiness faster and makes the product more effective. It takes 30 seconds and makes a noticeable difference, especially in the morning.</span>",
        "gg1vOTZxWgQ_text": "Step 1 — Cleanse first",
        "ggQay7_0R18_text": "<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:36px;\"><strong>Step 1 — Cleanse first</strong></span>",
        "gg91q9-JyhQ_text": "<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Always apply to a clean face. The skin around the eye is the thinnest on your entire body — it absorbs everything. Remove residue before you start.</span>",
        "ggf683RWjbT_text": "Step 2 — Apply",
        "ggyciH0gnK2_text": "<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:36px;\"><strong>Step 2 — Apply</strong></span>",
        "ggtMsuzvFc3_text": "<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Squeeze a tiny amount onto your fingertip — less than a pea. That's enough for both eyes. Dot it along the orbital bone — the curved edge of the eye socket, not the eyelid itself. Never directly under the lash line.</span><br><br>&nbsp;<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Use your ring finger only. It applies the least pressure of any finger. Tap gently in a circle from the inner corner outward, following the bone. Don't rub, don't drag. Pulling the skin around the eye accelerates exactly what you're trying to fix.</span><br><br><span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">More product does not mean better results. It sits on top of the skin and goes to waste. Less, applied correctly, works. More, applied wrong, doesn't.</span>",
        "ggGtAaYlwRQ_text": "Step 3 — Let it absorb",
        "ggwFyO5fsZD_text": "<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:36px;\"><strong>Step 3 — Let it absorb</strong></span>",
        "ggSvMUldtVE_text": "<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">60 seconds before applying anything else on top. The actives need direct contact with the skin.</span><br><br><span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Use morning, evening, or both.</span>",
        "gg50lSKjFA0_text": "<span style=\"background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:#17162E;font-size:px;\">What To Expect</span>",
        "ggwCdGlY-we_text": "Week 1–2",
        "ggnKgtsDXwv_text": "<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Puffiness reduces. The skin feels firmer. Dark circles don't disappear yet — but the hollow, tired look starts to lift.</span>",
        "ggPnTyC8Wnw_text": "Week 3–4",
        "ggLENM_VMAh_text": "<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Fine lines at the corners begin softening. You start looking rested even when you're not.</span>",
        "ggAAzj-iPZZ_text": "Week 6–8",
        "ggOX1w76kcs_text": "<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Dark circles and under-eye hollows visibly reduced. The eye area looks tighter. This is when people around you start noticing — without being able to say why.</span>",
        "gggFo5HWShx_text": "Month 3+",
        "ggeiOwctp3l_text": "<span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Structural improvement. One jar was a start. Three months is a real change.</span><br><span style=\"color:rgb(21,21,21);\">Consistency is everything. Don't run out mid-routine.</span>"
      }
    },
